  "body": "This is either a bug or intentional behavior. I'm not sure which.\r\n\r\nWhen you render a component wrapped with a `<React.StrictMode>` tag, the component's constructor and render functions will get called twice each. While this didn't cause any other noticeable problems, it did send me on a wild goose chase during a debugging session.\r\n\r\nHere's a codepen that reproduces the issue using React/ReactDOM 16.4.0:\r\nhttps://codepen.io/spudly_1470322188/pen/deBqbx?editors=1111",
